First, let's think about what the Riemann hypothesis means in this context. The Riemann hypothesis states that all non-trivial zeros of the Riemann zeta function $\zeta(s)$ have real part 1/2. Verifying this up to a certain height $H_0$ means checking that no zeros have real part different from 1/2 within the critical strip $0 < \text{Re}(s) < 1$ up to that height.

